This paper discusses the performance and limitations of Neural Networks, which is a common topic in the fields of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also addresses the issue of adversarial attacks, which falls under the category of Computer Security and Cryptography (cs.CR). The methodology proposed in the paper involves model checking, which is a technique commonly used in Software Engineering (cs.SE) for verifying the correctness of software systems. Finally, the paper discusses the implications of inaccurate results in safety-critical applications, which is a topic in the field of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
